column4: Principal\rkfuentes@carlsbadusd.net\rhttp://www.ches.schoolloop.com\r\r2018-19 School Accountability Report Card\r----Published During the 2019-20 School Year\r\rSchool Description\rThe CHE community is here to ignite a love of learning and help develop empathy
column6: and joy in each\rstudent. Through engaging activities
column9: all Calavera students\rwill grow in their abilities and hopefully come to realize their capabilities.\r\rCalavera Hills Elementary School (CHE) is a science
column12: and math (STEM) focused school\rthat provides unique learning opportunities to its students. CHE utilizes Project Lead the Way (PLTW) modules
column13: \ralong with project-based learning in conjunction with core adopted curriculum to provide a well-rounded\reducation beginning in kindergarten. Students will leave fifth grade with experiences in STEM curriculum
column15: and a readiness for the rigor of secondary school. CHE is a 1:1 device school.\r-\rSuch technology is integrated throughout the school day.\rCarlsbad Unified School District\r6225 El Camino RealTypes of Services Funded\rCarlsbad CA

D.\rworkstation, and the ability to print documents.\rSuperintendent\r\rMr. Chris Wright\rState Priority: School Climate\rAssistant Superintendent, Business\rThe SARC provides the following information relevant to the State priority: School Climate (Priority 6):\rServices\r•Pupil suspension rates;\rMr. Rick Grove•Pupil expulsion rates; and\rAssistant Superintendent,•Other local measures on the sense of safety.\rPersonnel Services\rSchool Safety Plan Dr. Robert Nye\rWe revise and update our school safety plan each year in the fall. Our current school safety plan meets all Assistant Superintendent,\rfederal, state, and district standards for a comprehensive school safety plan. It addresses prevention, planning, Instructional Services\rresponding, and recovering from possible threats (earthquakes, intruders,  fires) to ensure the safety of\rstudents, staff, and visitors. Our counselors, psychologists, and site administrators are extensively trained in\rthreat assessment techniques by nationally recognized experts in school-threat assessment. To ensure safety\ron our campus, a school site safety committee conducts inspections to identify potential hazards. We have\ralso developed a disaster preparedness plan, and we conduct regular fire and earthquake drills to familiarize\rstaff and students with emergency procedures. Our school site is also monitored for physical safety. Play\rstructures, sidewalks, and the school’s landscaping are maintained at a high standard for student safety and\rundergo regular inspections. A new visitor check-in system is being implemented, requiring all visitors to sign\rin and out.
